The paper discusses the effectiveness of anonymization in double-blind review, which is a process commonly used in software engineering (SE) and programming languages (PL) research. The study also involves asking reviewers to guess author identities, which relates to human-computer interaction (HC) and security and privacy (CR) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the advantages and disadvantages of revealing author identities, which could be relevant to information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.SE and cs.HC, followed by cs.CR, cs.IR, and cs.PL.
